LearnHub API Documentation

Postman collection OpenAPI spec

Introduction

The documentation

Base URL:

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

To authenticate requests, include an Authorization header with the value "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}".

All authenticated endpoints are marked with a requires authentication badge in the documentation below.

You can retrieve your token by visiting your dashboard and clicking Generate API token.

Received response

Example request: 
curl --request GET \
    --get "/admin/user" \
    --header "Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "/admin/user"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = '/admin/user';
$response = $client->get(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Authorization' => 'Bearer {YOUR_AUTH_KEY}',
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

import json

Login

POST
/admin/login

This endpoint enables users with admin role to sign in

Headers

Content-Type
Example:
application/json
Accept
Example:
application/json

Body Parameters

email
password
required
Example:
mitchel.olson@example.net
password
string
required
Example:
iure
Headers
:
:
Body
{ "email": "mitchel.olson@example.net", "password": "iure" }
Request failed with error

Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network. If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS. You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Received response

Example request: 
curl --request POST \
    "/admin/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"mitchel.olson@example.net\",
    \"password\": \"iure\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "/admin/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "mitchel.olson@example.net",
    "password": "iure"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = '/admin/login';
$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'email' => 'mitchel.olson@example.net',
            'password' => 'iure',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
import requests
import json

url = '/admin/login'
payload = {
    "email": "mitchel.olson@example.net",
    "password": "iure"
}
headers = {
  'Content-Type': 'application/json',
  'Accept': 'application/json'
}

response = requests.request('POST', url, headers=headers, json=payload)
response.json()

const url = new URL(
    "/content/blog-posts"
);

const params = {
    "title": "?title=learnhub",
    "tags": "?tags=[php,laravel,react]",
    "author": "?author=john",
    "sort": "?sort=title",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

    "Content-Type": "application/json",

    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'title' => '?title=learnhub',
            'tags' => '?tags=[php,laravel,react]',
            'author' => '?author=john',
            'sort' => '?sort=title',
        ],
    ]
);

print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Received response

Example request: 
curl --request GET \
    --get "/blog-posts?title=sapiente" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "/blog-posts"
);

const params = {
    "title": "sapiente",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$url = '/blog-posts';
$response = $client->get(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'query' => [
            'title' => 'sapiente',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));

Example:
application/json

string
required

required

nostrum

required

Received response

curl --request POST \
    "/contact" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \

    \"message\": \"nostrum\",

}"

const url = new URL(
    "/contact"
);

    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    "name": "aut",
    "email": "janelle.towne@example.org",
    "message": "nostrum",
    "cf-turnstile-response": "optio"
};

    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

$response = $client->post(
    $url,
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'name' => 'aut',
            'email' => 'janelle.towne@example.org',
            'message' => 'nostrum',
            'cf-turnstile-response' => 'optio',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
